      "writtenOn": "2020-04-24T23:27:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "IIUC, the exit code matters only for -complete-invocation-exit-codes and invocation.interrupted.\n\nOriginally, I thought rdb-stream would return\n- the exit code from the test process, OR\n- a special exit code, 1001, if rdb-stream was not able to run the test command for whatever reasons.\n\nHowever, this requires the user of rdb-stream, such as Swarming Task, to handle -complete-invocation-exit-codes.\n\nWhat I current have in mind is\n(1) rdb-stream always returns 0 or 1.\n- rdb-stream handles -complete-invocation-exit-codes\n- if rdb-stream was able to run the test command, and the test process exited with 0 or any of the exit codes listed in -complete-invocation-exit-codes, rdb-stream exits with 0. In any other cases, it exits with 1.\n\n(2) Swarming Task always marks the invocation.interrupted with !exit_code_from_rdb_stream.\n\nWDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "495fad4a_ca41b387",
